SIMPLE: expressive
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Expressive
<hw>Ex*press"ive</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>expressif</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Serving to express, utter,
or represent; indicative; communicative; -- followed by <xex>of</xex>;
<as>as, words <ex>expressive</ex> of his gratitude</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Each verse so swells <qex>expressive</qex> of her woes.</q>
<rj><qau>Tickell.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Full of expression; vividly representing the meaning
or feeling meant to be conveyed; significant; emphatic; <as>as,
<ex>expressive</ex> looks or words</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>You have restrained yourself within the list of too cold an adieu;
be more <qex>expressive</qex> to them.</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Through her <qex>expressive</qex> eyes her soul distinctly
spoke.</q> <rj><qau>Littelton.</qau></rj></p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Ex*press"ive*ly</wf>,<pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Ex*press"ive*ness</wf>,<pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>expressiveness</ent>⟦br⟧
